                    java.lang.String address)
             throws CustomExceptions.DocumentExistException,
                    CustomExceptions.ObligatoryFieldsException
        This method add an User in the ArrayList User of the class post:The ArrayList has to be initialized and the user has not be in the ArrayList before pre:The ArrayList will have an new User
        Parameters:
        typeDoc - is the String that represent the user's type of the document. It just can be the constants of the Class TypeDocuments
        numDoc - is the String that represent the number of the User's Document numDoc!=0 and numDoc!=" "
        name - is the String that represents the user's name name!=" "
        lastName - is the String that represents the user's last name lastName!=" "
        phone - is the String that represents the user's phone number phone!=0
        adress - is the String that represent the user's address
        Throws:
        CustomExceptions.DocumentExistException
        CustomExceptions.ObligatoryFieldsException

      • registTurn

        public java.lang.String registTurn(java.lang.String numDoc)
                            throws CustomExceptions.NotFoundException
        This method assign a turn for a User in the Arraylist pre: The user has to be in the ArrayList and it doesn't have a turn before post: The user will have assigned a consecutive turn
        Parameters:
        numDoc - is the String that represent the User's number of Document numDoc!=0 and numDoc!=" "
        Returns:
        turn is the String that represent the User's turn that was assigned
        Throws:
        CustomExceptions.NotFoundException - it is throwing when the user is not registered in the ArrayList
